We will now plot the data and interpret the results. I propose to keep the first 3 principal components - PC1: is a weighted average of running and jumping variables: all velocity variables, high jump and long jump. - PC2: is a weighted average with negative weights of results in throwing events: shot put, discus throw, javelin throw. - Probably by looking at this first two PCs we are able to distinguish between sprinters and throwers. - PC3: its seems a contrast between pole vault and highjump vs X100m (postive value).
